Despite several Hamas leaders being killed and the 1.7 million inhabitants of the Gaza Strip being imprisoned in one of the most desolate and densely populated corners of the planet, Israel has so far failed to destroy Hamas.
In fact, Hamas is gaining in the West Bank, which is controlled by the rival, moderate Palestinian group Fatah.
And Hamas leaders may come to the conclusion that they have the time on their side.
Just as Islamists have gained influence in the Arab world, Hamas has been able to attract powerful and wealthy friends to its side.
